natural problem: What is the greatest common divisor of $39$ and $91$?
natural solution: Listing the prime factors of $39$ and $91$, we have $39 = 3 \cdot 13$ and $91 = 7 \cdot 13$. The only prime common to both factorizations is $13$ (raised to the $1$st power), so the greatest common divisor must be $\boxed{13}$.

a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 What is the greatest common divisor of $39$ and $91$? The final Answer is 13
 ### Proof
 Listing the prime factors of $39$ and $91$, we have $39 = 3 \cdot 13$ and $91 = 7 \cdot 13$. The only prime common to both factorizations is $13$ (raised to the $1$st power), so the greatest common divisor must be $\boxed{13}$.
 *)

theorem
shows  "gcd 39 91 = 13"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
